  <compounddef id="RIGHT" kind="page">
    <compoundname>RIGHT</compoundname>
    <title>RIGHT$ Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">RIGHT$(string-expression,<sp/>integer-expression)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Returns the <bold>rightmost characters</bold> from a string. The second parameter specifies how many characters to return.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect1 id="RIGHT_1examples-111_1s1"><sect2 id="RIGHT_1examples-111_1s2"><sect3 id="RIGHT_1examples-111">
<title>Examples</title><para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>RIGHT$(&quot;RetroRocket&quot;,<sp/>6)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>&quot;Rocket&quot;</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Extract<sp/>file<sp/>extension</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">filename$<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;document.txt&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>RIGHT$(filename$,<sp/>3)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>&quot;txt&quot;</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Clip<sp/>to<sp/>last<sp/>10<sp/>characters</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">id$<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;USER-2025-SESSION-ABC123&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>RIGHT$(id$,<sp/>10)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>&quot;SESSION-ABC123&quot;</computeroutput> (truncated to fit length).</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3></sect2></sect1>
<sect1 id="RIGHT_1notes-110_1s1"><sect2 id="RIGHT_1notes-110_1s2"><sect3 id="RIGHT_1notes-110">
<title>Notes</title><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>If the requested length is greater than the string length, the entire string is returned.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>If the length is <computeroutput>0</computeroutput>, an empty string is returned.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Negative lengths cause an error.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Result is always a new string, leaving the original unchanged.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
